    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-03-06T01:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-03-06T01:00:00-05:00" n="66"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/7778: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Counselor of Embassy in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Peck</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-03-06T14:00:00+08:00"
                            >March 6, 1936—2 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received March 6—6:52 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>51. My 50, March 5, noon.</p>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>This office is reliably informed that at an emergency Cabinet meeting
                        called this morning to discuss the Communist situation in Shansi it was
                        announced that a threat had been received from Japanese Military Attaché
                        Isogai to the effect that the Japanese will not permit the sending of
                        Central Government troops into Shansi to oppose the Communists unless the
                        Chinese Government agrees to Hirota’s three point <pb facs="0170" n="75"
                            xml:id="pg_75"/> program and even in that case any troops thus
                        despatched must be withdrawn when their mission against the Communists is
                        completed.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>Repeated to Peiping and Ambassador at Shanghai.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Peck</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
